The paper discusses the use of software-defined networks and network function virtualization for IoT networks, which falls under the category of computer networks and internet architecture (cs.NI). It also covers security and management solutions, which could fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the complexity of network infrastructure, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses research challenges and open issues, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
